00:43:48.338 --> 00:43:52.218
therapies, whether it's checkpoint therapies like PD-1, PD-L1, which are also on

623
00:43:52.258 --> 00:43:55.938
the surface of the cancer cells and the T-cells, or whether there are small

624
00:43:56.058 --> 00:43:58.878
molecule kinase inhibitors like FGFR3 inhibitors.

625
00:43:58.937 --> 00:44:02.158
Every single one of the new therapies in bladder cancer goes after a cell surface

626
00:44:02.167 --> 00:44:06.128
protein. And so, of course, we're going to talk a little bit about EV, which is

627
00:44:06.198 --> 00:44:09.258
a ADC that targets the surface protein nectin-4.

628
00:44:09.648 --> 00:44:13.298
And in contrast to SG, which carries that topoisomerase

629
00:44:13.358 --> 00:44:16.678
inhibitor, EV actually carries an MMAE molecule, which is a

